{
  "texts": [
    "Stakeholders may have critical information that would be missed if researchers were to rely only on prior theories, experiments, and survey data.",
    "In fact, involving stakeholders can guide the development of interventions and policies that are relevant, effective and acceptable for them, ultimately leading to improved outcomes [28, 29].",
    "This is helpful for allocating research efforts to the most important problems and for ensuring interventions are targeted.",
    "Another research field where it is important to understand latent beliefs mediated by natural language is behavior change.",
    "The goal of this field is to promote beneficial behavior or reduce harmful behavior [30]."
  ]
}